OL,3,CWhat's behind the Budget tradition of
OL,4,Cthe chancellor's red box?
OL,6,FThe same wooden box, covered with
OL,7,Fscarlet leather and lined with black
OL,8,Fsatin, was hand-crafted in the 1860s
OL,9,Fand used for about 100 consecutive
OL,10,Fyears.
OL,12,FLord Callaghan broke with tradition in
OL,13,F1965 when he used a new box.
OL,15,FGordon Brown later became the second
OL,16,Fchancellor to use a new box for the
OL,17,FBudget in 1997. A new red box was then
OL,18,Fused again by George Osborne in 2011.
OL,20,FIs the red box only used for the
OL,21,FBudget?
