OL,3,CWhat's behind the Budget tradition of
OL,4,Cthe chancellor's red box?
OL,6,FRed boxes, also known as despatch
OL,7,Fboxes, are used on a daily basis by
OL,8,Fministers to transport official
OL,9,Fgovernment papers.
OL,11,FThey are lead-lined to protect papers
OL,12,Finside - a feature designed in the
OL,13,Fpast to ensure the box sank if it fell
OL,14,Foverboard a ship that had been
OL,15,Fcaptured.
OL,17,FThe despatch boxes are also embossed
OL,18,Fwith the royal cypher of the reigning
OL,19,Fmonarch, King Charles III, in gold.
